    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Jan 16/49</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir:-</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You used to come to <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> every once
                in a while and I was<lb/> hoping that I would soon have the<lb/> pleasure of meeting
                you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">However the news of my<lb/> being here, as well as my intention<lb/>
                to publish a journal for Jewish<lb/> interests has been brought to you<lb/> in the
                meantime.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I take the liberty of<lb/> writing to you directly in order to<lb/>
                prevent misunderstandings which<lb/> may be caused by the reports of<lb/>
                <del>this and</del> unqualified persons.<lb/> It is desirable that men of our<lb/>
                kind understand each other personally<lb/>
                <del>as well as</del> in order to further the cause for which we work.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Several people asked me<lb/> to publish my journal in both
                languages<lb/> —English and German—. But on the<lb/> one hand, I <sic>dont</sic>
                master the English<add>?</add><lb/> language well enough to write in</p>
            <p rend="The following is written at the top left corner of the page.">32A</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">2</p>
            <p>and on the other hand it would be<lb/> ignoring your fine publication. Some<lb/> may
                not like it so well (? <add>his</add> language<lb/> presumably) but I am convinced
                that I<lb/>
                <sic>wont</sic> improve a whole lot <sic>not</sic> matter<lb/> how hard I work. You
                will I know<lb/> do whatever you can for me. You<lb/> know the taste and the needs
                of<lb/> your readers so much better than<lb/> I do and most of us who hardly
                know<lb/> how much simpler it is to find fault<lb/> than to make it better
                themselves.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Some time next week<lb/> you will get the program of my<lb/>
                publication. I assure you that I will<lb/> accord to your Occident the <add>?</add>
                esteem<lb/> and the position which it deserves as<lb/> the older Jewish publication
                and due<lb/> to its esteemed <del>editors (coworkers)</del> collaborators.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our views may be different<lb/> but nothing shall be left undone
                    <add>on my part</add><lb/> to promote a friendly and congenial<lb/> working
                together for all we are<lb/> worth.</p>
            <pb n="3R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">3</p>
            <p>Such a working together will no<lb/> doubt turn out to be profitable<lb/> for the two
                of us. But time will<lb/> prove that.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It would make me<lb/> happy to get your assurance that<lb/> you are
                not contrary to my work<lb/> and that you want to collaborate<lb/> with me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName>
            </p>
            <p><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>February 16th 1849</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <date>24 Schebath 5609</date>
            </p>
